In the evening your mind won't stop whirring, you lie awake for hours each night, and by the time morgens comes, sleep is far from your mind even well before your alarm goes off.
If you suffer from these issues, you're in good company: According to the Robert Koch Institute, around a quarter of adults suffer from sleep disorders, and more than ten percent find that they häufig or always wake up not feeling refreshed.
viele people feel that their sleep throughout the night is unsatisfactory or inadequate, says Jens Wagenknecht, Member of the Board of the German Association of General Practicioners, who practices in Varel in Lower Saxony.
wann should you see your doctor about sleep disorders?
If, over the course of a month, you schläft poorly for at least three nights a week, and find that this impacts you during the day, you should see a doctor, advises Weeß.
They can impact in various unterschiedlich ways: You could be exhausted, tired, poorly rested, suffer from difficulties concentrating and staying alert, be irritable, have mood swings or physical complains such as stomach ache or headaches.
There are hardly any registered sleep doctors in Germany, emphasises Prof. Ingo Fietze, Head of the interdisziplinären Centre for Sleep Medicine at the Charité University Medicine Centre in Berlin.
Your doctor will examine you to see if the problems have a körperliche cause.
You don't have to vorbereiten for the examination at all.
"Just - bitte don't take an afternoon nap," says Fietze.
There are a fair few areas that can be adjusted to encourage a besseren night's sleep.
Weeß lists them: going to bed and getting up a regular times, not staying in bed too long, not sleeping during the day, not watching fernsehen to get to sleep, avoiding alcohol, and not looking at the clock during the night - because then you start working out times straight away, and that's not helpful at all.
